relevant_findings.description: Secret classified document describing the 201 System for intelligence file management
relevant_findings.direct_quote: The 201 system provides a method for identifying a person of specific interest to the Operations Directorate and for controlling and filing all pertinent information about that person.
relevant_findings.significance: Reveals internal CIA filing and tracking methodology for personnel of interest

relevant_findings.description: Detailed explanation of how intelligence files are indexed and maintained
relevant_findings.direct_quote: These are normally subjects of extensive reporting and CI investigation, prospective agents and sources, members of groups and organizations of continuing target interest
relevant_findings.significance: Provides insight into how intelligence agencies track and categorize individuals
Provides insight into CIA operational documentation and filing procedures

relevant_findings.direct_quote: Files on these may be kept in any desired order. Should such personalities become of general CS interest, they must be brought into the 201 system.
relevant_findings.significance: Reveals internal CIA documentation protocols for tracking individuals of interest
